Problem:
class Store {
  private int customers = 0;
  private int sales = 0;

  public void enterCustomer(int number) {
    this.customers += number;
  }

  public void makeSale(int soldItems) {
    this.sales += soldItems;
  }

  public int getCustomers() {
    return this.customers;
  }

  public int getSales() {
    return this.sales;
  }

  public void promotionalEvent(int discountRate) {
    if (discountRate > 20) {
      this.customers += 10;
      this.sales += 50;
    }
  }
}",

If the store runs a promotional event with a high discount rate, will there be an increase in the number of customers?
